    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm not sure I understand the use case here. We currently do not display the label/title, only the list of refinements. If there are no refinements because of the query (ie. no records have the fields on which the widget is supposed to add a refinement list), then we will display nothing.\n\nWhat did I get wrong here?\n\nIn any case, I would keep the widget the simple task of displaying the list. No label/title, no wrapper, no footer. This can be achieved with the underlying HTML markup, directly by the user. I would provide a way to know the current list of refinements from the outside, though. Maybe through an event and let the user toggle an `hidden` CSS class on the list based on that.\n\nOn the other hand, we need to be careful with \"we just let the user do this or that\". The main goal of this project was that the users did not have to do much. We might need to be more clear on what is included in the core widgets and will not be.\n",
